## üî¨ Technical Architecture: The LCES Decision Framework

The system's success derives from a three-layer architecture that separates strategic analysis from tactical execution, enabling consistent high-quality outputs even under time pressure and emotional stress.

### Layer 1: Constitutional Doctrine Repository

The foundation layer contains pre-analyzed legal frameworks for immunity doctrines, jurisdictional requirements, and procedural rules, enabling rapid identification of applicable legal standards without redundant research.

### Layer 2: Strategic Decision Engine

The middle layer evaluates case-specific facts against the doctrine repository to generate optimal pleading strategies, predicting judicial responses and identifying the path of least resistance through procedural obstacles.

### Layer 3: Execution and Compliance Interface

The surface layer translates strategic decisions into properly formatted legal documents, automated deadline tracking, and procedural checklists that ensure technical compliance with court rules and preserve all appellate issues.

